items.title: Attention Dividend Investors: 4 Stocks To Build Your Own Income Factory
3 S&P 500 Stocks Skating on Thin Ice
items.description: The S&P 500 (^GSPC) is often seen as a benchmark for strong businesses, but that doesn’t mean every stock is worth owning. Some companies face significant challenges, whether it’s stagnating growth, heavy debt, or disruptive new competitors.

items.title: The London Company Large Cap Vs. Russell 1000 Value Q1 2025 Commentary
items.description: The London Company Large Cap portfolio returned 2.4% during the quarter vs. a 2.1% increase in the Russell 1000 Value Index.
